==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Epiperipheral
<hw>Ep`i*pe*riph"er*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>epi-</ets> + <ets>peripheral</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>Connected with, or having its origin upon, the external surface of
the body; -- especially applied to the feelings which originate at the
extremities of nerves distributed on the outer surface, as the sensation
produced by touching an object with the finger; -- opposed to
<contr>entoperipheral</contr>.</def> <rj><au>H. Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epipetalous</ent>⟦br⟧
